updated File Manager bonus plugin.</p>\r<h3>File Manager Update</h3>\r<p>The File Manager bonus plugin has been updated to version 3.1.  It will be necessary to manually deactivate and delete the old version; and manually install and activate the new version.</p>\r<p>This can be done via the &#8220;Bonus&#8221; sub-menu page of WP Edit Pro.</p>\r<p>The update to the File Manager Plugin includes:</p>\r<ul>\r<li>Updated file manager to 9.9.2.</li>\r<li>Added option to allow sub-sites access to ONLY their respective WP Content uploads folder.</li>\r<li>Fixed &#8220;settings&#8221; link on plugins page when network activated.</li>\r<li>Added new menu page for File Manager options.</li>\r<li>Finalized language translation strings.</li>\r<li>Added tabs for options administration (settings page).</li>\r<li>Added multiple options for controlling various parts of the File Manager configuration.</li>\r<li>Added options for allowable file types.</li>\r<li>Added auto-update code; so future updates can be administered via the WP panel.</li>\r</ul>\r<h3>Add Media Button Update</h3>\r<p>A few new options have also been added to the &#8220;Editor&#8221; tab.</p>\r<p>These options apply to the &#8220;Add Media&#8221; button; just above the content editor.</p>\r<p>Options can now be set to control the default values used for media alignment, link and type.</p>\r<div id=\"attachment_1622\" style=\"width: 618px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"http://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/wpeditpro/~https://wpeditpro.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/add_media3.png\"><img src=\"https://wpeditpro.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/add_media3.png\" alt=\"WP Edit Pro Add Media Options\" width=\"608\" height=\"269\" class=\"size-full wp-image-1622\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">WP Edit Pro Add Media Options</p></div>\r<div style=\"margin-top:20px;\"></div>\r<div id=\"attachment_1616\" style=\"width: 302px\" class=\"wp-caption alignnone\"><a href=\"http://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/wpeditpro